{
  "local_port": 58254,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best hotels to stay at in San Francisco?",
  "response": "San Francisco offers a variety of excellent hotels for different preferences and budgets. Here are some highly recommended hotels in the city:\n\n1. **The Ritz-Carlton, San Francisco**\n   - Location: Nob Hill\n   - Features: Luxury accommodations, stunning views of the bay and city skyline, and a renowned spa. It's perfect for those seeking a high-end experience.\n\n2. **The Palace Hotel, a Luxury Collection Hotel**\n   - Location: Financial District\n   - Features: Historic charm with modern amenities, including the famous Garden Court restaurant. Ideal for those interested in a blend of history and luxury.\n\n3. **Four Seasons Hotel San Francisco**\n   - Location: SoMa (South of Market)\n   - Features: Elegant rooms, top-notch service, and proximity to major attractions like the Museum of Modern Art. Great for luxury travelers and families.\n\n4. **The Fairmont San Francisco**\n   - Location: Nob Hill\n   - Features: Iconic hotel with a rich history, stunning views, and a variety of dining options. A favorite among those who appreciate classic elegance.\n\n5. **Hotel Nikko San Francisco**\n   - Location: Union Square\n   - Features: Modern amenities, a great location near shopping and dining, and a fantastic Japanese restaurant. Suitable for business and leisure travelers.\n\n6. **The St. Regis San Francisco**\n   - Location: SoMa (South of Market)\n   - Features: Luxurious rooms, excellent dining options, and a central location. Perfect for those seeking a sophisticated and modern experience.\n\n7. **Argonaut Hotel**\n   - Location: Fisherman's Wharf\n   - Features: A nautical theme, comfortable rooms, and proximity to major tourist attractions. Great for families and those who want to be near the waterfront.\n\n8. **Hotel Zetta San Francisco**\n   - Location: SoMa (South of Market)\n   - Features: Trendy, tech-savvy hotel with a great vibe, and excellent amenities like a complimentary wine hour. Ideal for younger travelers and those looking for a modern, hip atmosphere.\n\n9. **The Westin St. Francis San Francisco on Union Square**\n   - Location: Union Square\n   - Features: Classic elegance, large rooms, and a prime location near shopping and theaters. Suitable for both business and leisure travelers.\n\n10. **The Clift Royal Sonesta Hotel**\n    - Location: Union Square\n    - Features: Modern design with a historic touch, a popular bar, and a central location. Great for those who enjoy a unique and vibrant atmosphere.\n\nThese hotels are among the best in San Francisco, each offering unique features and amenities to suit different preferences. Be sure to book in advance, especially during peak travel seasons, to secure the best rates and availability.",
